Restaurant Quality At Home

Sous Vide is a method in which food is sealed in plastic, placed in water, and then gently and slowly cooked at a precise temperature. Protected from the extreme heat of an oven or flame, it results in evenly cooked beef, pork, chicken, and fish that is irresistibly tender and bursting with flavor. The Chefman Precision Cooker makes it easier than ever to prepare dishes that are simply the best you ever had.

Read more

How To Use The Sous Vide


View larger

View larger

View larger

Step 1 : Prep and Seal

Place food in a food-grade sealed bag, vacuum-sealed or ziplock. Add seasonings or spices like herbs, butter, and garlic. For extra flavor, marinate food in fridge prior to sealing.

Step 2 : Cook your Food

Securely clip the sous vide to any deep heat-proof pot or container. Fill water level between MIN and MAX indicators marked on the sous vide. Connect to power, set time and temperature then immerse the sealed bag.

Step 3 : Sear and Enjoy!

Once the alarm beeps to signal the end of cooking time, finish your food by grilling, broiling or searing it in a piping-hot pan, adding a delicious caramelized texture and a more appetizing appearance. Enjoy your restaurant quality meal!

Product description

WHAT IS A SOUS VIDE? Simply put, Sous Vide is an easy, stress-free method of producing 5-star restaurant quality dishes using just a pot, some water, and food in a bag. Chefman Sous Vide helps home chefs master underwater cooking with submerged circulation technology that precisely controls the water temperature, ensuring meals from steak to fish and veggies to eggs never go above the perfect internal heat level, and resulting in a succulently juicy, evenly cooked dish that will impress family & friends alike. Long the domain of professional chefs and serious foodies, Sous Vide is finally accessible to the everyday consumer with Sous Vide by Chefman. The master of underwater cooking, Chefman Sous Vide's advanced even heating technology keeps water at the precise temperature needed for succulent Sous Vide results, locking in juices, flavor, and preserving the nutritional quality of food with incomparable taste and texture. (An available app makes the experience even more simple and seamless). Perfectly cooked steaks, juicy chicken, fall-off-the-bone ribs and vibrant veggies are just a few of the possibilities accessible with just the push of a button. The Sous Vide is also known as Suvide Cooker or Suvid Machine for the French style of cooking.

July 24, 2017

So proud of this Chefman Sous Vide

I've been looking into Sous Vide cooking for over a long time, I made a lot of research and I am so excited for this one and couldn't be happier with this purchase. We've used it everyday since I got it and just love it. You name it we've cooked it, Fish steak, roast, vegetables. Not a single complaint. And so Juicy and précised it’s wonderful, If you are considering this purchase, just be aware you can't use it to cook a meal in a hurry and you need to plan ahead. (Think of it like cooking with a crock pot... low temperature cooking over long periods of time ... slow and steady) .

Last night I said to myself, know what lets challenge this cooker with the tough meat challenge. One of claims of sous vide cooking is it can make the toughest cut of meat tender. So got to my butcher asked him for a cheap inexpensive cut of meat which was a chuck underblade steak (also sometimes called a bottom chuck steak)... these are cuts that all too often turn out really tough. Be aware that tough meats need to cook for a much longer period of time. Following the instructions for cooking a tough cut of beef to medium rare... we cooked ours at 149 degrees for 19 hours ( recommended time is 16 to 24 hours) . The result ... was a delicious melt in your mouth delight, no knife needed, cut it with the side of a fork dinner. Really amazing.

Also with this sous vide you don’t need any vacuum sealer or Food Saver type of appliance to use this cooker, Again I will reaped You DON’T need any, just take any bucket, pot or container you have at home put it in ANY zip lock bag with your favorite flavored species and bingo… after an Hr. or two you get your delicious steak…

Also don’t forget about club Chefman, in the box I got info how to access club Chefman with amazing super recipes it’s a real bonus…

 My son is a professional chef so I bought this for him as a Christmas present to have at home. Of course, Mom had to try it out and see how it worked before wrapping it up for him. LOL
I tried this product while cooking eggs and corn on the cob. I fill a very large pot with water to the max level on the device and turned it on. I had accidentally over-filled the pot making the water go past the overfill at the beginning, which caused the device to sound an alarm. This was an easy fix, I simply removed the excess water. I set the temperature to the desired temp and let it cook for several hours.
The food items were in Ziploc plastic bags and the air was removed (as much as possible).
After several hours, I tested the corn which was soft and ready to eat. The eggs were poached and not to the desired level we prefer, so they were returned to the stove for more cooking time.
For me as a beginner on this device, I think this is a very nice item to cook foods via water like a slow cooker. My son is a novice at this method as he does this all the time in his profession and uses a much larger device at his restaurant and has been looking for a small unit to use at home. So, if you wish to have restaurant quality foods served at home, this is the device for you.
